## Mandatory Workflow
1. Read `AGENTS.md` before starting work.
2. During `Discover`, `High-Level Architecture`, `Specify`, and `Plan`, do not use assumptions as substitutes for missing requirements; resolve ambiguity explicitly or mark the work item blocked.
3. Spec-Driven Development is mandatory by default for assistant-executed work; bypass only when the user explicitly says not to follow SDD for the requested task.
4. Start each new SDD work item with `make spec-scaffold ...`, which creates a dedicated non-default branch by default (`codex/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<slug>` unless overridden).
5. Execute the Spec-Driven Development lifecycle in order: `Discover -> High-Level Architecture -> Specify -> Plan -> Implement -> Verify -> Document -> Operate -> Publish`.
6. Change code, tests, docs, and contract-adjacent files together.
7. Keep platform-owned work in `make/platform.mk`, `make/platform/*.mk`, `scripts/bin/platform/**`, `scripts/lib/platform/**`, `apps/**`, and `docs/platform/**`.
8. Treat blueprint-managed paths as controlled surfaces and update them only intentionally:
   - `blueprint/**`
   - `docs/blueprint/**`
   - `scripts/bin/blueprint/**`
   - `scripts/lib/blueprint/**`
   - `scripts/templates/**`
   - `make/blueprint.generated.mk`
9. Run the required validation bundle for the changed scope before finishing.
10. Update `AGENTS.decisions.md` when scope, contracts, or operating policy change.
11. Update `AGENTS.backlog.md` when priorities or status change.
12. Do not run `git commit` or `git push` unless explicitly requested in the current conversation.

## Quality Hooks — Inner-Loop and Pre-PR Usage

The blueprint quality-hooks policy applies to this repository. All agent sessions MUST run with `QUALITY_HOOKS_KEEP_GOING=true` exported so that `quality-hooks-*` invocations aggregate independent failures instead of aborting on the first.

- **Per-slice gate**: `make test-unit-all` — run after every code edit within a slice.
- **Pre-PR gate**: `make quality-hooks-fast` — run at slice boundaries and before publishing.
- `QUALITY_HOOKS_FORCE_FULL=true` bypasses path-gating and phase-gating.

For the full policy (env vars, path-gating set, phase-gating rationale, failure-cascade caveat): see the blueprint `AGENTS.md` § Quality Hooks — Inner-Loop and Pre-PR Usage.

## SDD Artifacts
- Use `specs/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<work-item-slug>/` for work-item artifacts.
- Start new work items with `make spec-scaffold SPEC_SLUG=<work-item-slug>`; dedicated-branch creation is default and explicit opt-out requires `SPEC_NO_BRANCH=true`.
- Required documents per work item:
  - `architecture.md`
  - `spec.md`
  - `plan.md`
  - `tasks.md`
  - `traceability.md`
  - `graph.json`
  - `evidence_manifest.json`
  - `context_pack.md`
  - `pr_context.md`
  - `hardening_review.md`
- Start from `.spec-kit/templates/consumer/*`.
- Keep `.spec-kit/policy-mapping.md` aligned with this governance file and repository contracts.
- Keep `.spec-kit/control-catalog.json` as the control source and `.spec-kit/control-catalog.md` rendered from it.
- `architecture.md` is the high-level exploration workspace for each work item.
- Finalized architecture outcomes are recorded as ADRs under `docs/platform/architecture/decisions/`.
- Use the north-star architecture references:
  - `docs/platform/architecture/north_star.md`
  - `docs/platform/architecture/tech_stack.md`

## SDD Readiness Gate
- `Implement` may start only when `SPEC_READY=true` is explicitly recorded in the work-item spec.
- A work item is implementation-ready only when all are true:
  - Open questions count is `0`.
  - Unresolved alternatives count is `0`.
  - Unresolved TODO/TBD/TBC markers count is `0`.
  - Pending assumptions count is `0`.
  - Required sign-offs are approved (`Product`, `Architecture`, `Security`, `Operations`).
  - `ADR path` points to an existing ADR file and `ADR status` is approved.
- If required inputs are missing, mark the work item with `BLOCKED_MISSING_INPUTS` and keep `SPEC_READY=false`.
- Code assistants must not silently fill missing business or non-functional requirements in spec artifacts.

