## SDD Guardrails
- Capture non-functional requirements in `Discover` and `Specify` (security, observability, monitoring/alerting, reliability, operability).
- Keep architecture/style compliant with SOLID, Clean Architecture/Clean Code, and DDD adapted to your technology stack.
- Follow shift-left test automation: validate with the lowest valid test layer first, then escalate to integration/e2e only when boundary interactions require it.
- For filter or payload-transform logic, require positive-path unit coverage: a matching fixture/request value MUST return a record and preserve relevant output fields; empty-result-only assertions MUST NOT satisfy this gate.
- For work touching HTTP route handlers, query/filter logic, or new API endpoints, run local smoke with positive-path `curl` assertions before publish and capture `Endpoint | Method | Auth | Result` evidence in `pr_context.md`.
- Translate reproducible pre-PR smoke/`curl`/deterministic-check failures into failing automated tests first and turn them green with the fix in the same work item; document deterministic exceptions in publish artifacts.
- Define applicable `SDD-C-###` control IDs in each work-item spec and keep validation/evidence aligned with `.spec-kit/control-catalog.md`.
- Define stack profile and agent execution model explicitly before implementation.
- Apply managed-service-first policy for runtime capabilities in `stackit-*` profiles: prefer STACKIT managed services unless `spec.md` + ADR + `AGENTS.decisions.md` explicitly record an approved exception rationale.
- Define local-first runtime baseline explicitly (`Runtime profile`, local kube context policy, local provisioning stack, runtime identity baseline) and record approved exception rationale when deviating.
- Define and maintain the app onboarding minimum make-target contract in `plan.md` and `tasks.md`, including `infra-port-forward-start`, `infra-port-forward-stop`, and `infra-port-forward-cleanup`.
- For blueprint-caused defects, track upstream escalation lifecycle in the spec (`Upstream issue URL`, `Temporary workaround path`, `Replacement trigger`, `Workaround review date`) and remove workaround once upstream fix is adopted.

## Clarification Marker Policy
- Use `[NEEDS CLARIFICATION: ...]` markers when requirements are incomplete.
- Keep `SPEC_READY=false` until clarification markers are resolved.
- `Open clarification markers count` must be `0` before implementation.

## Hardening Review and Publish Gate
- Complete a repository-wide hardening review before publish and capture it in `hardening_review.md`.
- Required hardening sections:
  - `Repository-Wide Findings Fixed`
  - `Observability and Diagnostics Changes`
  - `Architecture and Code Quality Compliance`
  - `Proposals Only (Not Implemented)`
- Generate `pr_context.md` before opening PRs with:
  - `Summary`
  - `Requirement Coverage`
  - `Key Reviewer Files`
  - `Validation Evidence`
  - `Risk and Rollback`
  - `Deferred Proposals`
- Canonical hardening target: `make quality-hardening-review`.

## Normative Language Policy
- Normative sections must use deterministic language: `MUST`, `MUST NOT`, `SHALL`, `EXACTLY ONE OF`.
- Forbidden in normative sections: `should`, `may`, `could`, `might`, `either`, `and/or`, `as needed`, `approximately`, `etc.`.

## Definition of Done
- Behavior works in affected paths.
- Tests cover the behavior at the lowest valid layer.
- Docs (including Docusaurus/Mermaid views) and Make targets stay synchronized.
- Validation passes for the touched scope.
- No avoidable debt is left in touched consumer-owned areas.

## Quality Gates
- Fast gate: `make quality-hooks-fast`
- Full gate: `make quality-hooks-run`
- Strict audits: `make quality-hooks-strict`
- Infra validation: `make infra-validate`
- Docs build/smoke: `make docs-build` and `make docs-smoke`

### Consumer Extension Targets

Override in `platform.mk` without merge-conflict risk on blueprint upgrade:

| Target | When it runs | Tier |
|---|---|---|
| `quality-consumer-pre-push` | pre-push hook (always_run) | Tier 1/unit — fast tests before every push |
| `quality-consumer-ci` | final step of `quality-ci-blueprint` | Tier 2/component — tests acceptable in CI only |

Both default to no-op (`@true`). Override example in `platform.mk`:

```makefile
quality-consumer-pre-push:
	@$(MAKE) backend-test-unit

quality-consumer-ci:
	@$(MAKE) touchpoints-test-component
```

